[0m[49m[39m  172, 172[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  173, 173[0m:[39m[49m **Model versioning and rollback.** Before promoting a retrained model to the production endpoint, run shadow scoring for one to two weeks: score each discharge with both the current and candidate models, compare predictions, and validate that the candidate's calibration and discrimination meet minimum thresholds (AUC >= current model AUC - 0.02, calibration slope between 0.85 and 1.15). SageMaker Model Registry tracks model versions and approval status. Use SageMaker endpoint production variants for canary deployments. Always maintain the ability to roll back to the previous model version within minutes. A bad model deployment here has direct patient impact: under-prediction means high-risk patients miss interventions; over-prediction causes alert fatigue that erodes clinical trust.
[0m[49m[39m  174, 174[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  175, 175[0m:[39m[49m ### Prerequisites
[0m[49m[39m  176, 176[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  177, 177[0m:[39m[49m | Requirement | Details |
[0m[49m[39m  178, 178[0m:[39m[49m |-------------|---------|
[0m[49m[39m  179, 179[0m:[39m[49m | **AWS Services** | Amazon SageMaker, Amazon HealthLake, AWS Glue, Amazon EventBridge, AWS Step Functions, Amazon DynamoDB, Amazon SNS, Amazon S3, Amazon QuickSight |
[0m[49m[39m  180, 180[0m:[39m[49m | **IAM Permissions** | `sagemaker:InvokeEndpoint`, `healthlake:SearchWithGet`, `healthlake:ReadResource`, `glue:StartJobRun`, `dynamodb:PutItem`, `dynamodb:GetItem`, `sns:Publish`, `s3:GetObject`, `s3:PutObject`, `states:StartExecution`. All permissions should be scoped to specific resource ARNs (e.g., `sagemaker:InvokeEndpoint` targeting `arn:aws:sagemaker:{region}:{account}:endpoint/readmission-risk-*`). Use separate IAM roles for the scoring Lambda, training pipeline, and monitoring functions with distinct permission boundaries. |
[0m[49m[39m  181, 181[0m:[39m[49m | **BAA** | Required. All services handling PHI must be covered under your AWS BAA. HealthLake, SageMaker, DynamoDB, S3, Glue, Step Functions, EventBridge, SNS, and QuickSight are all HIPAA-eligible. |
[0m[49m[39m  182, 182[0m:[39m[49m | **Encryption** | S3: SSE-KMS for feature stores and model artifacts. DynamoDB: encryption at rest (default). HealthLake: AWS-managed or customer-managed KMS keys. SageMaker: KMS encryption for training data, model artifacts, and endpoint traffic. All inter-service communication over TLS. |
[0m[49m[39m  183, 183[0m:[39m[49m | **VPC** | Production: SageMaker endpoints, Glue jobs, and Lambda functions in VPC with VPC endpoints for S3 (gateway), DynamoDB (gateway), SageMaker Runtime (interface), CloudWatch Logs (interface), Step Functions/states (interface), and SNS (interface). HealthLake accessed via interface endpoint (verify regional availability; HealthLake has more limited regional availability than other services in this architecture). |
[0m[49m[39m  184, 184[0m:[39m[49m | **CloudTrail** | Enabled for all API calls. Critical for HIPAA audit trail: who accessed which patient's risk score, when, and from where. Note: DynamoDB data events log table name and API action but not item keys. Implement application-level audit logging (patient_id, requesting identity, timestamp) for patient-level access auditing required by HIPAA. |
[0m[49m[39m  185, 185[0m:[39m[49m | **Sample Data** | MIMIC-III or MIMIC-IV (publicly available ICU dataset with readmission outcomes). CMS Synthetic Public Use Files for claims-based features. Never use real PHI in development. Model validation on real patient data requires a HIPAA-compliant environment with the same security controls as production. |
[0m[49m[39m  186, 186[0m:[39m[49m | **Cost Estimate** | SageMaker real-time endpoint (ml.m5.large): ~$0.115/hour (~$83/month). Scoring latency: <200ms per patient. At 100 discharges/day, the per-discharge cost is ~$0.003. HealthLake: $0.60/GB stored + $0.09 per 1000 read operations. Glue: $0.44/DPU-hour for batch feature engineering. Feature assembly involves 5-7 FHIR queries per patient; parallelize independent queries to keep assembly latency under 1 second. |
[0m[49m[39m  187, 187[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  188, 188[0m:[39m[49m ### Ingredients
[0m[49m[39m  189, 189[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  190, 190[0m:[39m[49m | AWS Service | Role |
[0m[49m[39m  191, 191[0m:[39m[49m |------------|------|
[0m[49m[39m  192, 192[0m:[39m[49m | **Amazon SageMaker** | Model training (monthly), real-time scoring endpoint, model registry |
[0m[49m[39m  193, 193[0m:[39m[49m | **Amazon HealthLake** | FHIR-native clinical data store for real-time feature queries |
[0m[49m[39m  194, 194[0m:[39m[49m | **AWS Glue** | Batch feature engineering, historical feature computation, training data preparation |
[0m[49m[39m  195, 195[0m:[39m[49m | **Amazon EventBridge** | Discharge event ingestion and filtering |
[0m[49m[39m  196, 196[0m:[39m[49m | **AWS Step Functions** | Orchestrates the scoring workflow with error handling and retries |
[0m[49m[39m  197, 197[0m:[39m[49m | **Amazon DynamoDB** | Stores risk scores for real-time lookup by downstream systems |
[0m[49m[39m  198, 198[0m:[39m[49m | **Amazon SNS** | Delivers high-risk alerts to care transition teams |
[0m[49m[39m  199, 199[0m:[39m[49m | **Amazon S3** | Feature store (Parquet), model artifacts, training datasets, scoring audit logs |
[0m[49m[39m  200, 200[0m:[39m[49m | **Amazon QuickSight** | Readmission analytics dashboards for leadership and quality teams |
[0m[49m[39m  201, 201[0m:[39m[49m | **AWS KMS** | Encryption key management for all PHI-containing stores |
[0m[49m[39m  202, 202[0m:[39m[49m | **Amazon CloudWatch** | Monitoring, alerting on scoring failures, model performance metrics |
[0m[49m[39m  203, 203[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  204, 204[0m:[39m[49m <!-- TODO (TechWriter): Expert review A2 (MEDIUM). Clarify feature store architecture: for >100 discharges/day, pre-compute historical utilization features nightly via Glue into DynamoDB keyed by patient_id. Scoring workflow queries HealthLake only for current-encounter features + DynamoDB for pre-computed historical features. This hybrid keeps latency under 500ms. -->
[0m[49m[39m  205, 205[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  206, 206[0m:[39m[49m ### Code
[0m[49m[39m  207, 207[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  208, 208[0m:[39m[49m > **Reference implementations:** The following AWS sample repos demonstrate patterns used in this recipe:
[0m[49m[39m  209, 209[0m:[39m[49m >
[0m[49m[39m  210, 210[0m:[39m[49m > - [`amazon-healthlake-server-cdk`](https://github.com/aws-samples/amazon-healthlake-server-cdk): CDK constructs for deploying HealthLake with proper security configuration
[0m[49m[39m  211, 211[0m:[39m[49m > - [`amazon-sagemaker-examples`](https://github.com/aws/amazon-sagemaker-examples): SageMaker training and deployment patterns including XGBoost for healthcare use cases
[0m[49m[39m  212, 212[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  213, 213[0m:[39m[49m #### Step 1: Discharge Event Detection and Filtering
[0m[49m[39m  214, 214[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  215, 215[0m:[39m[49m **What this does:** Listens for ADT discharge events and filters to only qualified inpatient discharges that should be scored. Observation stays, planned readmissions, and transfers to other acute facilities are excluded.
[0m[49m[39m  216, 216[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  217, 217[0m:[39m[49m **What goes wrong if you skip it:** You score patients who shouldn't be scored (observation stays aren't subject to readmission penalties), waste compute on irrelevant events, and pollute your outcome tracking with non-qualifying encounters.
[0m[49m[39m  218, 218[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  219, 219[0m:[39m[49m ```
[0m[49m[39m  220, 220[0m:[39m[49m FUNCTION handle_discharge_event(event):
[0m[49m[39m  221, 221[0m:[39m[49m     // Parse the ADT message (HL7 A03 or FHIR Encounter update)
[0m[49m[39m  222, 222[0m:[39m[49m     patient_id = event.patient_identifier
[0m[49m[39m  223, 223[0m:[39m[49m     encounter_type = event.encounter_class
[0m[49m[39m  224, 224[0m:[39m[49m     discharge_disposition = event.disposition
[0m[49m[39m  225, 225[0m:[39m[49m     length_of_stay = event.discharge_date - event.admit_date
[0m[49m[39m  226, 226[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  227, 227[0m:[39m[49m     // Filter: only score qualifying inpatient discharges
[0m[49m[39m  228, 228[0m:[39m[49m     IF encounter_type NOT IN ["inpatient", "acute"]:
[0m[49m[39m  229, 229[0m:[39m[49m         LOG "Skipping non-inpatient encounter for patient {patient_id}"
[0m[49m[39m  230, 230[0m:[39m[49m         RETURN null
[0m[49m[39m  231, 231[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  232, 232[0m:[39m[49m     // Exclude transfers to other acute facilities (not true discharges)
[0m[49m[39m  233, 233[0m:[39m[49m     IF discharge_disposition IN ["transfer_acute", "left_ama"]:
[0m[49m[39m  234, 234[0m:[39m[49m         LOG "Skipping transfer/AMA for patient {patient_id}"
[0m[49m[39m  235, 235[0m:[39m[49m         RETURN null
[0m[49m[39m  236, 236[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  237, 237[0m:[39m[49m     // Exclude very short stays (likely observation misclassified)
[0m[49m[39m  238, 238[0m:[39m[49m     IF length_of_stay < 1 day:
[0m[49m[39m  239, 239[0m:[39m[49m         LOG "Skipping sub-24hr stay for patient {patient_id}"
[0m[49m[39m  240, 240[0m:[39m[49m         RETURN null
[0m[49m[39m  241, 241[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  242, 242[0m:[39m[49m     // Qualified discharge: trigger scoring workflow
[0m[49m[39m  243, 243[0m:[39m[49m     RETURN {
[0m[49m[39m  244, 244[0m:[39m[49m         patient_id: patient_id,
[0m[49m[39m  245, 245[0m:[39m[49m         encounter_id: event.encounter_id,
[0m[49m[39m  246, 246[0m:[39m[49m         discharge_date: event.discharge_date,
[0m[49m[39m  247, 247[0m:[39m[49m         primary_diagnosis: event.primary_diagnosis,
[0m[49m[39m  248, 248[0m:[39m[49m         discharge_disposition: discharge_disposition
[0m[49m[39m  249, 249[0m:[39m[49m     }
[0m[49m[39m  250, 250[0m:[39m[49m ```
[0m[49m[39m  251, 251[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  252, 252[0m:[39m[49m #### Step 2: Feature Assembly from Clinical Data
[0m[49m[39m  253, 253[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  254, 254[0m:[39m[49m **What this does:** Queries multiple data sources to assemble the complete feature vector for the discharged patient. Combines real-time clinical data from the current encounter with historical utilization patterns.
[0m[49m[39m  255, 255[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  256, 256[0m:[39m[49m **What goes wrong if you skip it:** The model receives incomplete or stale data, producing unreliable risk scores. Missing features (especially prior utilization history) dramatically reduce predictive accuracy.
[0m[49m[39m  257, 257[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  258, 258[0m:[39m[49m ```
[0m[49m[39m  259, 259[0m:[39m[49m FUNCTION assemble_features(discharge_info):
[0m[49m[39m  260, 260[0m:[39m[49m     patient_id = discharge_info.patient_id
[0m[49m[39m  261, 261[0m:[39m[49m     encounter_id = discharge_info.encounter_id
[0m[49m[39m  262, 262[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  263, 263[0m:[39m[49m     // --- Current Encounter Features ---
[0m[49m[39m  264, 264[0m:[39m[49m     // Query HealthLake for the index admission details
[0m[49m[39m  265, 265[0m:[39m[49m     encounter = FHIR_SEARCH("Encounter", id=encounter_id)
[0m[49m[39m  266, 266[0m:[39m[49m     conditions = FHIR_SEARCH("Condition", encounter=encounter_id)
[0m[49m[39m  267, 267[0m:[39m[49m     medications = FHIR_SEARCH("MedicationRequest", encounter=encounter_id)
[0m[49m[39m  268, 268[0m:[39m[49m     labs = FHIR_SEARCH("Observation", encounter=encounter_id, category="laboratory")
[0m[49m[39m  269, 269[0m:[39m[49m     procedures = FHIR_SEARCH("Procedure", encounter=encounter_id)
[0m[49m[39m  270, 270[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  271, 271[0m:[39m[49m     current_features = {
[0m[49m[39m  272, 272[0m:[39m[49m         length_of_stay: encounter.length_of_stay_days,
[0m[49m[39m  273, 273[0m:[39m[49m         admission_source: encounter.admission_source,  // ED, elective, transfer
[0m[49m[39m  274, 274[0m:[39m[49m         discharge_disposition: encounter.discharge_disposition,
[0m[49m[39m  275, 275[0m:[39m[49m         primary_diagnosis_code: encounter.primary_diagnosis.icd10,
[0m[49m[39m  276, 276[0m:[39m[49m         diagnosis_count: COUNT(conditions),
[0m[49m[39m  277, 277[0m:[39m[49m         procedure_count: COUNT(procedures),
[0m[49m[39m  278, 278[0m:[39m[49m         icu_days: calculate_icu_days(encounter),
[0m[49m[39m  279, 279[0m:[39m[49m         discharge_medication_count: COUNT(medications WHERE status="active"),
[0m[49m[39m  280, 280[0m:[39m[49m         high_risk_medications: COUNT(medications WHERE code IN HIGH_RISK_MED_LIST),
[0m[49m[39m  281, 281[0m:[39m[49m         // Lab values at discharge (most recent)
[0m[49m[39m  282, 282[0m:[39m[49m         albumin_last: most_recent_value(labs, code="1751-7"),
[0m[49m[39m  283, 283[0m:[39m[49m         creatinine_last: most_recent_value(labs, code="2160-0"),
[0m[49m[39m  284, 284[0m:[39m[49m         hemoglobin_last: most_recent_value(labs, code="718-7"),
[0m[49m[39m  285, 285[0m:[39m[49m         sodium_last: most_recent_value(labs, code="2951-2"),
[0m[49m[39m  286, 286[0m:[39m[49m         bnp_last: most_recent_value(labs, code="42637-9")
[0m[49m[39m  287, 287[0m:[39m[49m     }
[0m[49m[39m  288, 288[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  289, 289[0m:[39m[49m     // --- Historical Utilization Features ---
[0m[49m[39m  290, 290[0m:[39m[49m     // Look back 12 months for prior utilization patterns
[0m[49m[39m  291, 291[0m:[39m[49m     lookback_start = discharge_info.discharge_date - 365 days
[0m[49m[39m  292, 292[0m:[39m[49m     prior_encounters = FHIR_SEARCH("Encounter",
[0m[49m[39m  293, 293[0m:[39m[49m         patient=patient_id,
[0m[49m[39m  294, 294[0m:[39m[49m         date_range=[lookback_start, discharge_info.discharge_date],
[0m[49m[39m  295, 295[0m:[39m[49m         type="inpatient")
[0m[49m[39m  296, 296[0m:[39m[49m     prior_ed_visits = FHIR_SEARCH("Encounter",
[0m[49m[39m  297, 297[0m:[39m[49m         patient=patient_id,
[0m[49m[39m  298, 298[0m:[39m[49m         date_range=[lookback_start, discharge_info.discharge_date],
[0m[49m[39m  299, 299[0m:[39m[49m         type="emergency")
[0m[49m[39m  300, 300[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  301, 301[0m:[39m[49m     history_features = {
[0m[49m[39m  302, 302[0m:[39m[49m         admissions_past_6mo: COUNT(prior_encounters WHERE date > now - 180 days),
[0m[49m[39m  303, 303[0m:[39m[49m         admissions_past_12mo: COUNT(prior_encounters),
[0m[49m[39m  304, 304[0m:[39m[49m         ed_visits_past_6mo: COUNT(prior_ed_visits WHERE date > now - 180 days),
[0m[49m[39m  305, 305[0m:[39m[49m         prior_30day_readmission: ANY(prior_encounters WHERE
[0m[49m[39m  306, 306[0m:[39m[49m             days_since_prior_discharge <= 30),
[0m[49m[39m  307, 307[0m:[39m[49m         days_since_last_admission: days_between(
[0m[49m[39m  308, 308[0m:[39m[49m             most_recent(prior_encounters).discharge_date,
[0m[49m[39m  309, 309[0m:[39m[49m             discharge_info.discharge_date)
[0m[49m[39m  310, 310[0m:[39m[49m     }
[0m[49m[39m  311, 311[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  312, 312[0m:[39m[49m     // --- Comorbidity Features ---
[0m[49m[39m  313, 313[0m:[39m[49m     // Calculate Elixhauser comorbidity index from all active conditions
[0m[49m[39m  314, 314[0m:[39m[49m     all_conditions = FHIR_SEARCH("Condition", patient=patient_id, status="active")
[0m[49m[39m  315, 315[0m:[39m[49m     comorbidity_features = {
[0m[49m[39m  316, 316[0m:[39m[49m         elixhauser_score: calculate_elixhauser(all_conditions),
[0m[49m[39m  317, 317[0m:[39m[49m         has_chf: any_condition_in_group(all_conditions, "CHF"),
[0m[49m[39m  318, 318[0m:[39m[49m         has_diabetes: any_condition_in_group(all_conditions, "DIABETES"),
[0m[49m[39m  319, 319[0m:[39m[49m         has_copd: any_condition_in_group(all_conditions, "COPD"),
[0m[49m[39m  320, 320[0m:[39m[49m         has_ckd: any_condition_in_group(all_conditions, "CKD"),
[0m[49m[39m  321, 321[0m:[39m[49m         has_depression: any_condition_in_group(all_conditions, "DEPRESSION"),
[0m[49m[39m  322, 322[0m:[39m[49m         total_chronic_conditions: COUNT(all_conditions WHERE category="chronic")
[0m[49m[39m  323, 323[0m:[39m[49m     }
[0m[49m[39m  324, 324[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  325, 325[0m:[39m[49m     // --- Demographic Features ---
[0m[49m[39m  326, 326[0m:[39m[49m     patient = FHIR_SEARCH("Patient", id=patient_id)
[0m[49m[39m  327, 327[0m:[39m[49m     demographic_features = {
[0m[49m[39m  328, 328[0m:[39m[49m         age: calculate_age(patient.birth_date),
[0m[49m[39m  329, 329[0m:[39m[49m         sex: patient.gender,
[0m[49m[39m  330, 330[0m:[39m[49m         insurance_type: patient.coverage_type,  // Medicare, Medicaid, Commercial
[0m[49m[39m  331, 331[0m:[39m[49m         zip_deprivation_index: lookup_adi(patient.address.postal_code)
[0m[49m[39m  332, 332[0m:[39m[49m     }
[0m[49m[39m  333, 333[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  334, 334[0m:[39m[49m     // Combine all feature groups into single vector
[0m[49m[39m  335, 335[0m:[39m[49m     RETURN merge(current_features, history_features,
[0m[49m[39m  336, 336[0m:[39m[49m                  comorbidity_features, demographic_features)
[0m[49m[39m  337, 337[0m:[39m[49m ```
[0m[49m[39m  338, 338[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  339, 339[0m:[39m[49m #### Step 3: Model Scoring
[0m[49m[39m  340, 340[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  341, 341[0m:[39m[49m **What this does:** Passes the assembled feature vector to the trained XGBoost model and returns a readmission probability between 0 and 1.
[0m[49m[39m  342, 342[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  343, 343[0m:[39m[49m **What goes wrong if you skip it:** Obviously you don't get a risk score. But more subtly, if you skip the preprocessing and validation step, you'll send malformed features to the model and get garbage predictions without any error signal.
[0m[49m[39m  344, 344[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  345, 345[0m:[39m[49m ```
[0m[49m[39m  346, 346[0m:[39m[49m FUNCTION score_patient(feature_vector):
[0m[49m[39m  347, 347[0m:[39m[49m     // Validate feature completeness
[0m[49m[39m  348, 348[0m:[39m[49m     required_features = ["length_of_stay", "admissions_past_6mo",
[0m[49m[39m  349, 349[0m:[39m[49m                          "elixhauser_score", "age", "discharge_medication_count"]
[0m[49m[39m  350, 350[0m:[39m[49m     missing = [f FOR f IN required_features IF feature_vector[f] IS NULL]
[0m[49m[39m  351, 351[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  352, 352[0m:[39m[49m     IF COUNT(missing) > 2:
[0m[49m[39m  353, 353[0m:[39m[49m         LOG_WARNING "Too many missing features for patient, using fallback score"
[0m[49m[39m  354, 354[0m:[39m[49m         RETURN {probability: null, method: "insufficient_data", missing: missing}
[0m[49m[39m  355, 355[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  356, 356[0m:[39m[49m     // Handle missing values (model expects specific sentinel values)
[0m[49m[39m  357, 357[0m:[39m[49m     FOR each feature IN feature_vector:
[0m[49m[39m  358, 358[0m:[39m[49m         IF feature.value IS NULL:
[0m[49m[39m  359, 359[0m:[39m[49m             feature.value = -999  // XGBoost handles this as missing
[0m[49m[39m  360, 360[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  361, 361[0m:[39m[49m     // Invoke the SageMaker endpoint
[0m[49m[39m  362, 362[0m:[39m[49m     response = SAGEMAKER_INVOKE(
[0m[49m[39m  363, 363[0m:[39m[49m         endpoint_name = "readmission-risk-v2",
[0m[49m[39m  364, 364[0m:[39m[49m         content_type = "text/csv",
[0m[49m[39m  365, 365[0m:[39m[49m         body = feature_vector_to_csv(feature_vector)
[0m[49m[39m  366, 366[0m:[39m[49m     )
[0m[49m[39m  367, 367[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  368, 368[0m:[39m[49m     raw_probability = PARSE_FLOAT(response.body)
[0m[49m[39m  369, 369[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  370, 370[0m:[39m[49m     // Apply calibration (Platt scaling learned during training)
[0m[49m[39m  371, 371[0m:[39m[49m     calibrated_probability = platt_scale(raw_probability,
[0m[49m[39m  372, 372[0m:[39m[49m         A = CALIBRATION_PARAMS.A,
[0m[49m[39m  373, 373[0m:[39m[49m         B = CALIBRATION_PARAMS.B)
[0m[49m[39m  374, 374[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  375, 375[0m:[39m[49m     RETURN {
[0m[49m[39m  376, 376[0m:[39m[49m         probability: calibrated_probability,
[0m[49m[39m  377, 377[0m:[39m[49m         raw_score: raw_probability,
[0m[49m[39m  378, 378[0m:[39m[49m         method: "xgboost_v2",
[0m[49m[39m  379, 379[0m:[39m[49m         model_version: response.model_version,
[0m[49m[39m  380, 380[0m:[39m[49m         scored_at: NOW()
[0m[49m[39m  381, 381[0m:[39m[49m     }
[0m[49m[39m  382, 382[0m:[39m[49m ```
[0m[49m[39m  383, 383[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  384, 384[0m:[39m[49m #### Step 4: Risk Stratification and Intervention Routing
[0m[49m[39m  385, 385[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  386, 386[0m:[39m[49m **What this does:** Converts the raw probability into an actionable risk tier and determines which intervention pathway the patient should receive based on their risk level and contributing factors.
[0m[49m[39m  387, 387[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  388, 388[0m:[39m[49m **What goes wrong if you skip it:** A probability of 0.42 means nothing to a care transition nurse. They need "high risk, prioritize for home health referral." Without stratification and routing, the model output sits in a database and nobody acts on it.
[0m[49m[39m  389, 389[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  390, 390[0m:[39m[49m ```
[0m[49m[39m  391, 391[0m:[39m[49m FUNCTION stratify_and_route(score_result, feature_vector, discharge_info):
[0m[49m[39m  392, 392[0m:[39m[49m     probability = score_result.probability
[0m[49m[39m  393, 393[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  394, 394[0m:[39m[49m     // Stratify into tiers based on calibrated thresholds
[0m[49m[39m  395, 395[0m:[39m[49m     // Thresholds are set based on intervention capacity and cost-effectiveness
[0m[49m[39m  396, 396[0m:[39m[49m     IF probability >= 0.35:
[0m[49m[39m  397, 397[0m:[39m[49m         risk_tier = "HIGH"
[0m[49m[39m  398, 398[0m:[39m[49m         intervention_level = "intensive"
[0m[49m[39m  399, 399[0m:[39m[49m     ELSE IF probability >= 0.20:
[0m[49m[39m  400, 400[0m:[39m[49m         risk_tier = "MEDIUM"
[0m[49m[39m  401, 401[0m:[39m[49m         intervention_level = "standard"
[0m[49m[39m  402, 402[0m:[39m[49m     ELSE:
[0m[49m[39m  403, 403[0m:[39m[49m         risk_tier = "LOW"
[0m[49m[39m  404, 404[0m:[39m[49m         intervention_level = "routine"
[0m[49m[39m  405, 405[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  406, 406[0m:[39m[49m     // Determine primary risk drivers for intervention targeting
[0m[49m[39m  407, 407[0m:[39m[49m     // (from model feature importance for this specific patient)
[0m[49m[39m  408, 408[0m:[39m[49m     risk_drivers = get_top_contributing_features(feature_vector, top_n=5)
[0m[49m[39m  409, 409[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  410, 410[0m:[39m[49m     // Route to appropriate intervention based on tier + drivers
[0m[49m[39m  411, 411[0m:[39m[49m     interventions = []
[0m[49m[39m  412, 412[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  413, 413[0m:[39m[49m     IF risk_tier == "HIGH":
[0m[49m[39m  414, 414[0m:[39m[49m         // All high-risk patients get a nurse follow-up call within 48 hours
[0m[49m[39m  415, 415[0m:[39m[49m         interventions.ADD("nurse_callback_48hr")
[0m[49m[39m  416, 416[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  417, 417[0m:[39m[49m         // Specific interventions based on risk drivers
[0m[49m[39m  418, 418[0m:[39m[49m         IF "discharge_medication_count" IN risk_drivers OR
[0m[49m[39m  419, 419[0m:[39m[49m            "high_risk_medications" IN risk_drivers:
[0m[49m[39m  420, 420[0m:[39m[49m             interventions.ADD("pharmacist_med_reconciliation")
[0m[49m[39m  421, 421[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  422, 422[0m:[39m[49m         IF "admissions_past_6mo" IN risk_drivers:
[0m[49m[39m  423, 423[0m:[39m[49m             interventions.ADD("care_transition_program_enrollment")
[0m[49m[39m  424, 424[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  425, 425[0m:[39m[49m         IF discharge_info.primary_diagnosis IN CHF_CODES:
[0m[49m[39m  426, 426[0m:[39m[49m             interventions.ADD("remote_weight_monitoring")
[0m[49m[39m  427, 427[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  428, 428[0m:[39m[49m         IF feature_vector.zip_deprivation_index > 8:
[0m[49m[39m  429, 429[0m:[39m[49m             interventions.ADD("social_work_assessment")
[0m[49m[39m  430, 430[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  431, 431[0m:[39m[49m     ELSE IF risk_tier == "MEDIUM":
[0m[49m[39m  432, 432[0m:[39m[49m         interventions.ADD("automated_check_in_call_day_7")
[0m[49m[39m  433, 433[0m:[39m[49m         interventions.ADD("ensure_followup_scheduled")
[0m[49m[39m  434, 434[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  435, 435[0m:[39m[49m     // Store the complete risk assessment
[0m[49m[39m  436, 436[0m:[39m[49m     risk_assessment = {
[0m[49m[39m  437, 437[0m:[39m[49m         patient_id: discharge_info.patient_id,
[0m[49m[39m  438, 438[0m:[39m[49m         encounter_id: discharge_info.encounter_id,
[0m[49m[39m  439, 439[0m:[39m[49m         discharge_date: discharge_info.discharge_date,
[0m[49m[39m  440, 440[0m:[39m[49m         probability: probability,
[0m[49m[39m  441, 441[0m:[39m[49m         risk_tier: risk_tier,
[0m[49m[39m  442, 442[0m:[39m[49m         risk_drivers: risk_drivers,
[0m[49m[39m  443, 443[0m:[39m[49m         interventions: interventions,
[0m[49m[39m  444, 444[0m:[39m[49m         model_version: score_result.model_version,
[0m[49m[39m  445, 445[0m:[39m[49m         scored_at: score_result.scored_at,
[0m[49m[39m  446, 446[0m:[39m[49m         ttl: discharge_info.discharge_date + 45 days  // Keep 15 days past window
[0m[49m[39m  447, 447[0m:[39m[49m         // TODO (TechWriter): Expert review S4 (MEDIUM). Add note about compliance
[0m[49m[39m  448, 448[0m:[39m[49m         // retention requirements. 45-day TTL is operationally sound but scores that
[0m[49m[39m  449, 449[0m:[39m[49m         // influenced clinical decisions may need 6-10 year retention. Consider
[0m[49m[39m  450, 450[0m:[39m[49m         // archiving to S3 before TTL deletion.
[0m[49m[39m  451, 451[0m:[39m[49m     }
[0m[49m[39m  452, 452[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  453, 453[0m:[39m[49m     // Write to DynamoDB for downstream system access
[0m[49m[39m  454, 454[0m:[39m[49m     DYNAMODB_PUT("readmission-risk-scores", risk_assessment)
[0m[49m[39m  455, 455[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  456, 456[0m:[39m[49m     // Notify care team for high-risk patients
[0m[49m[39m  457, 457[0m:[39m[49m     // IMPORTANT: SNS messages with patient IDs + clinical indicators = PHI.
[0m[49m[39m  458, 458[0m:[39m[49m     // Restrict topic subscriptions to HIPAA-compliant endpoints only
[0m[49m[39m  459, 459[0m:[39m[49m     // (Lambda, SQS within VPC, or HTTPS endpoints under your BAA).
[0m[49m[39m  460, 460[0m:[39m[49m     // Never use email/SMS subscriptions for messages containing patient data.
[0m[49m[39m  461, 461[0m:[39m[49m     // If email alerts are needed, send minimal content ("1 new high-risk
[0m[49m[39m  462, 462[0m:[39m[49m     // discharge requires review") with a link to the secure dashboard.
[0m[49m[39m  463, 463[0m:[39m[49m     IF risk_tier == "HIGH":
[0m[49m[39m  464, 464[0m:[39m[49m         SNS_PUBLISH(
[0m[49m[39m  465, 465[0m:[39m[49m             topic = "high-risk-discharge-alerts",
[0m[49m[39m  466, 466[0m:[39m[49m             message = format_alert(risk_assessment),
[0m[49m[39m  467, 467[0m:[39m[49m             attributes = {
[0m[49m[39m  468, 468[0m:[39m[49m                 "risk_tier": "HIGH",
[0m[49m[39m  469, 469[0m:[39m[49m                 "primary_diagnosis": discharge_info.primary_diagnosis,
[0m[49m[39m  470, 470[0m:[39m[49m                 "facility": discharge_info.facility_id
[0m[49m[39m  471, 471[0m:[39m[49m             }
[0m[49m[39m  472, 472[0m:[39m[49m         )
[0m[49m[39m  473, 473[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  474, 474[0m:[39m[49m     RETURN risk_assessment
[0m[49m[39m  475, 475[0m:[39m[49m ```
[0m[49m[39m  476, 476[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  477, 477[0m:[39m[49m #### Step 5: Outcome Tracking and Model Monitoring
[0m[49m[39m  478, 478[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  479, 479[0m:[39m[49m **What this does:** Monitors actual 30-day readmission outcomes against predictions, detects model drift, and triggers retraining when performance degrades.
[0m[49m[39m  480, 480[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  481, 481[0m:[39m[49m **What goes wrong if you skip it:** Your model silently degrades over time as patient populations shift, coding practices change, or new care programs alter readmission patterns. Without monitoring, you won't know your predictions are wrong until someone manually audits them months later.
[0m[49m[39m  482, 482[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  483, 483[0m:[39m[49m ```
[0m[49m[39m  484, 484[0m:[39m[49m FUNCTION track_outcomes_and_monitor():
[0m[49m[39m  485, 485[0m:[39m[49m     // Run daily: check for readmissions among previously scored patients
[0m[49m[39m  486, 486[0m:[39m[49m     scored_patients = DYNAMODB_QUERY("readmission-risk-scores",
[0m[49m[39m  487, 487[0m:[39m[49m         discharge_date BETWEEN (today - 31 days) AND (today - 30 days))
[0m[49m[39m  488, 488[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  489, 489[0m:[39m[49m     FOR each scored_patient IN scored_patients:
[0m[49m[39m  490, 490[0m:[39m[49m         // Check if patient was readmitted within 30 days
[0m[49m[39m  491, 491[0m:[39m[49m         readmissions = FHIR_SEARCH("Encounter",
[0m[49m[39m  492, 492[0m:[39m[49m             patient = scored_patient.patient_id,
[0m[49m[39m  493, 493[0m:[39m[49m             type = "inpatient",
[0m[49m[39m  494, 494[0m:[39m[49m             date_range = [scored_patient.discharge_date,
[0m[49m[39m  495, 495[0m:[39m[49m                          scored_patient.discharge_date + 30 days])
[0m[49m[39m  496, 496[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  497, 497[0m:[39m[49m         // Exclude planned readmissions using CMS algorithm
[0m[49m[39m  498, 498[0m:[39m[49m         unplanned = FILTER(readmissions, is_unplanned_readmission)
[0m[49m[39m  499, 499[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  500, 500[0m:[39m[49m         actual_outcome = 1 IF COUNT(unplanned) > 0 ELSE 0
[0m[49m[39m  501, 501[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  502, 502[0m:[39m[49m         // Store outcome for model evaluation
[0m[49m[39m  503, 503[0m:[39m[49m         DYNAMODB_UPDATE("readmission-risk-scores",
[0m[49m[39m  504, 504[0m:[39m[49m             key = scored_patient.encounter_id,
[0m[49m[39m  505, 505[0m:[39m[49m             set actual_readmitted = actual_outcome,
[0m[49m[39m  506, 506[0m:[39m[49m             set outcome_date = NOW())
[0m[49m[39m  507, 507[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  508, 508[0m:[39m[49m     // Weekly: calculate model performance metrics
[0m[49m[39m  509, 509[0m:[39m[49m     recent_scores = QUERY_LAST_30_DAYS_WITH_OUTCOMES()
[0m[49m[39m  510, 510[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  511, 511[0m:[39m[49m     metrics = {
[0m[49m[39m  512, 512[0m:[39m[49m         auc_roc: calculate_auc(recent_scores.probability, recent_scores.actual),
[0m[49m[39m  513, 513[0m:[39m[49m         calibration_slope: calculate_calibration(recent_scores),
[0m[49m[39m  514, 514[0m:[39m[49m         brier_score: calculate_brier(recent_scores),
[0m[49m[39m  515, 515[0m:[39m[49m         observed_rate_high_tier: rate(recent_scores WHERE tier="HIGH"),
[0m[49m[39m  516, 516[0m:[39m[49m         observed_rate_low_tier: rate(recent_scores WHERE tier="LOW"),
[0m[49m[39m  517, 517[0m:[39m[49m         total_scored: COUNT(recent_scores),
[0m[49m[39m  518, 518[0m:[39m[49m         total_readmitted: SUM(recent_scores.actual)
[0m[49m[39m  519, 519[0m:[39m[49m     }
[0m[49m[39m  520, 520[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  521, 521[0m:[39m[49m     // Publish metrics to CloudWatch
[0m[49m[39m  522, 522[0m:[39m[49m     CLOUDWATCH_PUT_METRICS("ReadmissionModel", metrics)
[0m[49m[39m  523, 523[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  524, 524[0m:[39m[49m     // Alert if performance degrades
[0m[49m[39m  525, 525[0m:[39m[49m     IF metrics.auc_roc < 0.65 OR metrics.calibration_slope < 0.8:
[0m[49m[39m  526, 526[0m:[39m[49m         SNS_PUBLISH("model-performance-alerts",
[0m[49m[39m  527, 527[0m:[39m[49m             "Readmission model performance degraded. AUC: {metrics.auc_roc}. "
[0m[49m[39m  528, 528[0m:[39m[49m             "Consider retraining.")
[0m[49m[39m  529, 529[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  530, 530[0m:[39m[49m     RETURN metrics
[0m[49m[39m  531, 531[0m:[39m[49m ```
[0m[49m[39m  532, 532[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  533, 533[0m:[39m[49m > **Curious how this looks in Python?** The pseudocode above covers the concepts. If you'd like to see sample Python code that demonstrates these patterns using boto3, check out the [Python Example](chapter07.05-python-example). It walks through each step with inline comments and notes on what you'd need to change for a real deployment.
[0m[49m[39m  534, 534[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  535, 535[0m:[39m[49m ---
[0m[49m[39m  536, 536[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  537, 537[0m:[39m[49m ## Expected Results
[0m[49m[39m  538, 538[0m:[39m[49m 
